<TITLE> New war crime investigation agency by Mar 26 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 18 (bdnews24.com)  A new agency responsible for investigating war crimes will be formed before March 26, law minister Shafique Ahmed said on Thursday. At the same time, another special court to prosecute war crimes would be established, he said. Shafique was talking to reporters after meeting with home minister Sahara Khatun at her office. "The investigation agency will consist of 12 members and will be led by a retired inspector general of police," the minister said. The war crime tribunals will be led by a Supreme Court justice, Shafique said. "Those who were accused of committing crimes against humanity will be tried," the minister said. He also confirmed that the prosecution would be held under the International Crimes (Tribunals) Act 1973. The War Crimes Committee of the International Bar Association (IBA) has recently given a legal opinion stating that the 1973 Act contains "significant omissions" regarding protection of rights of those on trial and "out of date" definitions of war crimes, and proposed 17 changes. bd
